This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with clock synchronization in Wireless Sensor Networks. It could also belong to the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY) as it proposes an enhanced solution to improve the Virtual High-resolution Timer. Additionally, it could belong to the sub-category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) as it deals with synchronization in a distributed system. It could also belong to the sub-category of Embedded Systems (cs.ET) as it deals with low-power oscillators and hardware resources. Finally, it could belong to the sub-category of Architecture (cs.AR) as it proposes an innovative solution to overcome the tradeoff between resolution and energy consumption.
